    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-10-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="55"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                <head>55. Memorandum of conversation, October 6, between Ambassador Sanz de
                    Santamaría and <persName corresp="#p_CWD_1">Coerr</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d55fn1">Colombian request for additional
                        internal security aid. Confidential. 2 pp. <gloss target="#t_DOS_1"
                            >DOS</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_CF_1">CF</gloss>,
                        721.5–MSP/10–661.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1961-10-06">October 6,
                            1961</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d55-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d55-1"/>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Colombian Request for Additional Internal Security Aid</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>Mr. Carlos Sanz de Santamaría, Ambassador of Colombia</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_ARA_1">ARA</gloss>—Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CWD_1"
                            >Coerr</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_ARA_1">ARA</gloss>/EST—Mr. Lancaster</item>
                </list>
                <p>Ambassador Sanz stated that he had come in under renewed personal instructions
                    from President <persName corresp="#p_LCA_1">Lleras</persName> to reiterate
                    Colombia’s need <pb facs="0314" n="139" type="typeset" xml:id="pg_139"/> for
                    additional military aid for internal security purposes. He referred to his
                    conversation on this subject with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_WRF_1"
                        >Woodward</persName> on September 20 and stated that President <persName
                        corresp="#p_LCA_1">Lleras</persName> continued to attach a high priority to
                    this problem.</p>
                <p>In his response to a question from Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CWD_1"
                        >Coerr</persName>, the Ambassador stated that he was not prepared to specify
                    individual items of equipment needed, although it was clear that light transport
                    aircraft had to be obtained to cope with outbreaks of banditry in isolated
                    regions such as that now troubling the Colombian Government in the Vichada area.
                    He indicated that the various types of equipment the Colombian Government
                    desired were listed in a memorandum which he had given to the Secretary last
                    spring (this memorandum was enclosed with the Department’s A–146 to Bogota of
                    April 24).</p>
                <p>(On October 9 Ambassador Sanz telephoned Mr. Lancaster to say that he had
                    received the following list of items on which the Colombian Government placed
                    highest priorities in equipping its forces for internal security operations:</p>
                <p>Infantry small arms:</p>
                <quote>
                    <p>4048 M1 rifles</p>
                    <p>888 M1 carbines</p>
                    <p>270 30 caliber machine guns</p>
                    <p>432 45 caliber sub-machine guns</p>
                    <pb facs="d55-2" n="2" type="facsimile" xml:id="d55-2"/>
                    <p>Transport aircraft:</p>
                    <p>6 SA–16 Amphibians</p>
                    <p>4 C–47</p>
                    <p>3 C–54</p>
                </quote>
                <p>The Ambassador stated that the Colombian Army Chief of Staff, General Alberto
                    Ruiz Novoa, would be discussing these and other priority problems facing the
                    Colombian Armed Forces in the Department of Defense on October 10 and 11.)</p>
            </div>
